  "prompt": "Who was Billy the Kid and why is he famous?",
  "response": "Billy the Kid, born Henry McCarty (later known as William H. Bonney), was a notorious American outlaw and gunman of the Old West. He was born on November 23, 1859, and died on July 14, 1881. He gained fame for his involvement in the Lincoln County War in New Mexico Territory, his skills as a gunslinger, and his ability to evade capture.\n\n### Key Facts About Billy the Kid:\n1. **Lincoln County War**: Billy the Kid became widely known for his role in this conflict (1878\u20131881), a violent feud between rival factions in Lincoln County, New Mexico. He aligned with the \"Regulators,\" a group opposing powerful businessmen who monopolized trade in the region.\n\n2. **Notoriety as an Outlaw**: He was reputed to have killed up to 21 men, though the actual number is likely closer to 9. His ability to escape from custody multiple times added to his legend.\n\n3. **Capture and Escape**: In 1881, he was captured by Sheriff Pat Garrett and sentenced to hang for the murder of Sheriff William Brady. However, he famously escaped from jail, killing two deputies in the process.\n\n4. **Death**: Billy the Kid was ultimately shot and killed by Pat Garrett in Fort Sumner, New Mexico, at the age of 21. The circumstances of his death and his legend have been debated and romanticized ever since.\n\n### Why He\u2019s Famous:\nBilly the Kid became an iconic figure of the American Old West due to his youthful appearance, quick draw, and dramatic life story. He has been immortalized in numerous books, films, and folklore, often depicted as a romanticized antihero\u2014a symbol of rebellion and outlaw life. His legend continues to captivate people as a representation of the lawlessness and adventure of the Wild West.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
